Sentencas: Effects of Nb-doping on the stability and electrochemical performance of SrCo0.2Fe0.8O3-delta were studied.
Titulo: Effects of niobium doping on the stability of SrCo0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy and electrical conductivity measurements show that SrCo0.2Fe0.8O3-delta cathode has excellent electrochemical performance, while further Nb-doping reduces the performance of cathodes.
Titulo: Effects of niobium doping on the stability of SrCo0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Microstructure evolution reveals that Nb-doping suppresses the formation of impurity particles on the surface of cathodes.
Titulo: Effects of niobium doping on the stability of SrCo0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Good chemical compatibility between SrCo0.2Fe0.8O3-delta with GDC powders is confirmed by X-ray powder diffraction measurements.
Titulo: Effects of niobium doping on the stability of SrCo0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Results of temperature programmed desorption, thermogravimetric and thermal expansion coefficients tests indicate that Nb-doping improves the structural and chemical stability of SrCo(0.2)Fe(0.8)O(3-delta )cathodes because of the decrease of the concentration of oxygen vacancies in the crystal lattices.
Titulo: Effects of niobium doping on the stability of SrCo0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
